{"TopicId":130985,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Larger Landing Legs","CreatedByName":"royying","CreatedById":20591,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-29T18:56:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"royying","CreatedById":20591,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-29T18:56:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was trying to recover my ascent stage, and this happen...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;.;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/liIwsCX.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022liIwsCX.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think KSP need larger landing legs for big craft\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Armisael","CreatedById":152425,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-29T19:39:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...have you considered putting the legs on the side of that so it\u0027s low and wide instead of tall and narrow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StarManta","CreatedById":57805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-29T19:54:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222385207\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130985\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221454096342\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152425\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Armisael\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Armisael said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...have you considered putting the legs on the side of that so it\u0027s low and wide instead of tall and narrow?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t really work for an ascent stage...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Armisael","CreatedById":152425,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-29T20:31:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe drag from legs on a stage that size is trivial to counteract with engine gimbal or fins (and yes, I\u0027ve done it). You\u0027d need legs an order of magnitude larger than anything we have now that make that stage feasible to land on end anyways\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-30T03:24:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIssues with this particular ship aside:\u00A0 there\u0027s certainly a good case in the game for having some bigger landing legs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLots of good discussion here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/76787-bigger-landing-legs/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RocketSquid","CreatedById":152665,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-30T03:31:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck out \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/117527-105-wipalpha-lithobrake-exploration-technologies-031-2016-01-11/#comment-2101126\u0022\u003ELithobrake Exploration Technologies\u003C/a\u003E by Necrobones. It adds bigger parachutes, service bays, lander cans, and of course legs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-30T05:15:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222385266\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130985\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221454099478\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152425\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Armisael\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Armisael said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe drag from legs on a stage that size is trivial to counteract with engine gimbal or fins (and yes, I\u0027ve done it). You\u0027d need legs an order of magnitude larger than anything we have now that make that stage feasible to land on end anyways\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think you are getting the point, he is trying to land the ascent stage (SpaceX Style), not parachute it down.\u00A0 You can\u0027t use the main engines with landing legs on the side.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-30T05:16:13Z\u0022 title=\u002201/30/2016 05:16  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Alshain\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}